## Creational Patterns

### Builder Pattern
Used heavily in Java: `StringBuilder`, `HttpRequest.Builder`, Lombok `@Builder`

```java
// Without Builder — telescoping constructors are ugly
new Pizza("large", true, false, true, false);

// With Builder — readable and safe
Pizza pizza = Pizza.builder()
    .size("large")
    .cheese(true)
    .pepperoni(true)
    .build();
```

### Factory Method
Spring's `BeanFactory`, `DriverManager.getConnection()`, `Calendar.getInstance()`

```java
public interface NotificationSender {
    void send(String message);
}

// Factory decides which implementation to create
public class NotificationFactory {
    public static NotificationSender create(String type) {
        return switch (type) {
            case "email" -> new EmailSender();
            case "sms"   -> new SmsSender();
            case "push"  -> new PushSender();
            default -> throw new IllegalArgumentException(type);
        };
    }
}
```

