## Structural Patterns

### Decorator Pattern
Java I/O streams are classic decorators. Spring's `HttpServletRequestWrapper`.

```java
// Core component
InputStream raw = new FileInputStream("data.bin");

// Decorate with buffering
InputStream buffered = new BufferedInputStream(raw);

// Decorate with decompression
InputStream gzipped = new GZIPInputStream(buffered);

// Each layer adds behavior without modifying the original
```

### Proxy Pattern
Spring AOP, JDK Dynamic Proxy, CGLIB — almost everything in Spring is a proxy!

```java
@Service
public class UserService {
    @Transactional // Spring wraps this in a proxy that manages transactions
    public void saveUser(User user) { ... }
}
// The @Transactional bean you get injected is a PROXY, not the real UserService
```

## Behavioral Patterns

### Observer / Event Pattern
Spring's `ApplicationEventPublisher`, `@EventListener`

```java
// Event
public class OrderCreatedEvent {
    private final Order order;
}

// Publisher
@Service
public class OrderService {
    @Autowired ApplicationEventPublisher events;

    public void createOrder(Order order) {
        repo.save(order);
        events.publishEvent(new OrderCreatedEvent(order)); // fire & forget
    }
}

// Listener
@Component
public class EmailListener {
    @EventListener
    public void onOrder(OrderCreatedEvent e) {
        emailService.sendConfirmation(e.getOrder());
    }
}
```

